  "texts": [
    "Among these, 100 pathologists (46.5%) employed LLMs or chatbots in their professional activities, whereas 115 participants (53.5%) did not.",
    "The latter group featured a more females and individuals aged between 41 and 55 years compared to the group of users, with this difference being statistically significant (P=0.03).",
    "Table 1: Respondent characteristics Characteristics Users (N=100) Non-users (N=115) Pvalue Age < 30 years 9 (9%) 5 (4.3%) 0,17 30-40 years 49 (49%) 47 (40.9%) 0,23 41-55 years 29 (29%) 50 (43.5%) 0.03* > 56 years 13 (13%) 13 (11.3%) 0,43 Current position Pathologist, academic 48 (48%) 55 (47.8%) 0,98 Pathologist, nonacademic 33 (33%) 43 (37.4%) 0,5 Pathology trainee 19 (19%) 17 (14.8%) 0,41 Gender Male 58 (58%) 50 (43.5%) 0.03* Female 42 (42%) 65 (56.5%) 0.03* Geographical distribution Asia 42 (42%) 46 (40%) 0,77 Europe 40 (40%) 52 (45.2%) 0,44 North America 11 (11%) 6 (5.2%) 0,12 South America 4 (4%) 8 (7%) 0,35 Africa 1 (1) 2 (1.7%) 0,64 Oceania 2 (2%) 1 (0.9%) 0,48 *Statistically significant difference The user group exhibited a significantly greater understanding of coding skills, generative AI, and LLMs than the non-user group (P<0.01).",
    "In particular, academic pathologists demonstrated the highest level of understanding in digital pathology and LLMs (P=0.02).",
    "Conversely, pathology trainees who constituted about 20% of the users cohort reported lower levels of understanding, particularly in digital pathology and LLMs."
